<h4>1.5.6 Related Systems: Lantiv Scheduling Studio 7</h4>
<p> <i>Lantiv Scheduling Studio 7</i> is a scheduling and timetabling tool developed by Lantiv.
The software is aimed specifically at K-12 schools, universities, and medical centers.
Lantiv is especially suited for university scheduling because of flexible timings, conflict 
alerts and mutli-user web access.</p>
<p> Lantiv falls short without an automatic scheduling solution, but has many customization options
and a web interface.</p>
<ul class="inner_list"><b>Good Features:</b>
   <li>Multi-user web access</li>
   <li>Import from CSV, XML, Microsoft Access DB, and HTML</li>
   <li>Tabbed interface for multiple schedules</li>
   <li>Assign instructors, classrooms, and times to generated schedules</li>
   <li>Course conflict alerts</li>
   <li>Drag and drop</li>
   <li>Direct editing of schedules</li>
</ul>
<ul class="inner_list"><b>Bad Features:</b>
<li>While the application has a web platform, the desktop software is Windows-only</li>
<li>User interface looks cluttered and confusing to manage</li>
<li>Export feature is limited</li>
</ul>
<ul class="inner_list"><b>Missing Features:</b>
   <li>PDF schedule export</li>
   <li>Professor preferences</li>
   <li>Registered student voting for possible courses</li>
   <li>Automatic schedule generation</li>
   <li>Customizable running time restraints</li>
</ul>
